centralize /ˈsɛntrəˌlaɪz/

(centralizing,centralized,centralizes) BRIT also  centralise 

1. V-T To centralize a country, state, or organization means to create a system in which one central group of people gives instructions to regional groups. 使归中央控制; 集权的 

例： In the mass production era, multinational firms tended to centralize their operations. 在大规模生产时期，跨国公司倾向于集中运营。 

2. centralization N-UNCOUNT 集权化 

例： ...public hostility to central banks and the centralization of power. …公众对中央银行及集权的敌意。

